To illustrate how the LMDI works, some related variables are listed in Table 2. The aggregate industrial SO2 or NOx discharges are expressed as Y in Eq. 1. It is decomposed as the economic output effect (G), the industrial structure effect (S), and the intensity effect (I). I can somewhat reflect the technological level’s progress (Sun 1998) and can be further divided into the effects of cleaner production (C) and pollution abatement (A). C is the production of the two pollutants per unit of GDP, and A is the ratio of the pollutant’s discharge divided by the production’s amount. Therefore, C and A can somewhat reflect the developmental status of cleaner production technologies (CPTs) and pollution abatement technologies (PATs), respectively. The CPT focuses on the management of these pollutants’ sources and the reuse of resources during the process of production, whereas PAT only focuses on the pollution end-controlling.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
